This paper focuses on the performance evaluation of a communication decoder, specifically the Generalized Approximate Message Passing Decoder, for different channels and parameters. This falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the transmission and decoding of information. Additionally, the use of i.i.d matrices for constructing codewords suggests a focus on networked communication (cs.NI) and the evaluation of performance suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.MM). Finally, the study of sparse superposition codes suggests a focus on sparse modeling (cs.SI).
